  "prompt": "When is it likely that the proposed extended maternity leave from 12 to 26 weeks will be implemented for private sectors in India?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the implementation of extended maternity leave from 12 to 26 weeks in the private sector in India would depend on various factors, including legislative processes and government priorities. The Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act, which already provided for this extension in certain cases, was passed in 2017, but there are ongoing discussions and proposals about extending these benefits more broadly to the private sector.\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information on any developments regarding this proposal, I recommend checking official government releases or reputable news sources. The timeline for such policy changes can be uncertain and is influenced by political, economic, and social factors.",
